                                      - Kaludram Aderlas<br>
<br>
<br>
So what does TLC have anything to do with Roleplaying?  I thought roleplaying is interaction between characters (be it pc or npc) in an IN-CHARACTER manner.  I am NOT talking about speaking &quot;thou&quot; &quot;thee&quot; &quot;ye&quot; and those old english stuff.  I am talking about if you are a shadowknight of Hate, you behave like one (not some goodie two shoe paladin-wanna-be).  I frankly don't see how TLC hampers Roleplaying.<br>
<br>
However, TLC does the following:<br>
<br>
1. hampers the ability to endlessly camp and farm a certain item<br>
2. forces people to plan for items that they desire around their level.  This indirectly &quot;punishes&quot; those who level up too quickly and never got around doing their quest at the approiate lvl.<br>
3. forces high level players to &quot;hire&quot; others of apporiate lvls to acquire the items high lvler want.<br>
<br>
Does TLC make this server harder to play and enjoy all the quests out there?  Yes, it does.<br>
<br>
Does TLC hampers seriously one's ability to roleplay?  I doubt it.<br>
<br>
<br>
p.s of course this is my personal view and I am not saying that my version of Roleplaying is the standard in which roleplaying is judged upon.  Everyone has their own view of &quot;roleplaying&quot;, but seriously, quest isn't the ONLY component of roleplaying.  Saying &quot;With TLC in place one cannot roleplay&quot; is a bit overboard. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/01 3:29:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=821.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TLC Petition (TO KEEP IT)</span><hr size=1> I see nothing wrong with going to spoiler sites to learn info.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Roleplaying is how you react to your situations your presented with in game and in character</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  If a quest or quest item is so very important that you absolutely need to have it then look up the info for it.  All other quests do as you stumble upon them.<br>
<br>
Just becase you already know the outcome of a quest does not change the fact you can still have fun roleplaying with it.  Sure the magic of exploration is slightly diminished, but then again its all dependent on ones out look.  <br>
<br>
Why would you complain that you CAN'T do a certain quest if you don't even know what it yeilds?  Verant has done a excelent job of making sure the apropriate level character can do the apropriate quest.  If you can't do it chances are you don't need it, so don't worry about it.  <br>
